output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of Sport and exercise sciences, 1 years after graduation, PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION AND DEFENCE - COMPULSORY SOCIAL SECURITY was the most common industry for White and Asian ethnicity graduates, HUMAN HEALTH AND SOCIAL WORK ACTIVITIES was the most common industry for and Black ethnicity graduates, FINANCIAL AND INSURANCE ACTIVITIES was the most common industry for and Mixed ethnicity graduates, MANUFACTURING was the most common industry for and Other ethnicity graduates, and ADMINISTRATIVE AND SUPPORT SERVICE ACTIVITIES was the most common industry for and Not known ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was ADMINISTRATIVE AND SUPPORT SERVICE ACTIVITIES where Not known ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Black ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion.

The industry with the largest range in median earnings was INFORMATION AND COMMUNICATION where Not known ethnicity graduates the highest median earnings (£26,900) and Mixed ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£22,300).

The group with the highest median earnings was Asian ethnicity graduates in the HUMAN HEALTH AND SOCIAL WORK ACTIVITIES industry (median earnings of £28,100).

output.sankeytext1:
